This paper is about entity resolution (ER), which is a subfield of database management (cs.DB). The proposed framework involves a combination of human and machine efforts, which is a common theme in artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses risk analysis and prioritization, which are techniques commonly used in information retrieval (cs.IR). The framework also involves human-computer interaction and user experience, which falls under human-computer interaction (cs.HC). Finally, the paper discusses the performance of the proposed framework, which involves machine learning and optimization techniques (cs.LG).
